~ farmer
if quest_done("turnips")
	Farmer Bramble: Bless you for finding my turnips. The Meadows feel safer already.
elif quest_stage("turnips") == 2
	Farmer Bramble: You found them?! By the old fence — of course. Thank you kindly!
	do complete_quest("turnips")
	Farmer Bramble: Take this for your trouble.
elif quest_active("turnips")
	Farmer Bramble: Still looking? Try the turnip patch over to the east.
else
	Farmer Bramble: My turnips have been... misplaced. Borrowed-without-asking, I suspect.
	Farmer Bramble: Could you have a look around the Meadows for me?
	do start_quest("turnips")
=> END


~ vice_principal
VICE_PRINCIPAL.exe: A Form 7-B is required before any conflict may proceed. PER DISTRICT POLICY.
VICE_PRINCIPAL.exe: ...You have not filed one. We will resolve this through the proper channels.
=> END


~ vice_principal_defeated
VICE_PRINCIPAL.exe: Forms... depleted. Policy buffer... underrun. Sys-tem... yiel-ding.
Vice Principal: Oh — goodness. Where am I? Did I... did I assign you a detention just now?
Vice Principal: That wasn't me. That was the *policy* wearing my lanyard. Thank you for switching it off.
=> END


~ apologetic_merchant
if quest_done("apologetic_merchant")
	The Apologetic Merchant: Sorry again. And thank you. Sorry.
elif quest_active("apologetic_merchant")
	The Apologetic Merchant: We've made it to the edge? Oh — sorry, and thank you! So sorry.
	do complete_quest("apologetic_merchant")
else
	The Apologetic Merchant: So sorry to bother you. Could you walk with me a while? I get nervous.
	do start_quest("apologetic_merchant")
=> END
